-- Four Arab Countries Provide 74% of Foreign Investment in Iraq's Kurdistan
-- Caroline Alexander
-- 2010-07-21T09:55:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/four-arab-countries-provide-74-of-foreign-investment-in-iraq-s-kurdistan.html

          
          
             Arab states accounted for about 74
percent of the $3.6 billion of foreign investment in the semi-
autonomous Kurdistan region of northern Iraq over the past two
years, data from the  Kurdistan Regional Government  shows.  
 Since August 2008, four Arab nations have invested almost
$2.7 billion, the KRG said in a statement on its website.  
 Kuwait topped the list of foreign investors, with more than
$1.5 billion. Lebanon invested almost $760 million, Egyptian
investments reached $350 million and Jordan invested close to
$29 million, according to the statement.  
